<seg id=1> Jiang Zemin Says Preparation For Military Work Involves Good Militia First </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> XINHUA NEWS AGENCY WIRE Beijing, Sept. 1 (Ge Yumin reporting): Jiang Zemin, head of state and chairperson of the Central Military Commission, spoke today at the Zhongnanhai conference attended by some of the country's local militias who are preparing for military work. He stressed that each level of the local party committees and each level of the departments of government and military must pay attention both to the larger picture in terms of the work of the party and the country, and to a prolonged period of stability. He also placed emphasis on being a good member of the militia as preparation for military work. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Jiang Zemin said that the militia are both citizens and soldiers, not only preserving the country's safety and serving as an important force for maintaining the unity of the homeland, but also preserving the stability of society and promoting a strong force for the development of two cultures. </seg>
<seg id=4> Each level of the local party committees and each level of the departments of government and military should fully move this grand militia and the armed forces to enthusiasm and creativity, making their contribution to deepening reform, promoting development, and maintaining stability, he said. </seg>
<seg id=5> Further, each army unit should provide a reliable guarantee of security for reform, development and stability. They should actively join in with local economic development, and work hard to promote the collective prosperity of the people. </seg>
<seg id=6> What is needed is to strengthen unity between the military and the political, and between the army and the people. Only then will people of each ethnicity truly breathe together in a common destiny, heart to heart. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> Also present were Liu Huaqing, vice-chairperson of the Central Military Commission, Military Commission members Zhang Wannian, Yu Yongbo, Fu Quanyou, and leaders from the three divisions of the People's Liberation Army and the Military Commission general office. </seg>
</p>
